.SH NAME
DBIx::Class::Storage::DBI::SQLAnywhere::Cursor \- GUID Support for SQL Anywhere
over DBD::SQLAnywhere
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This class is for normalizing GUIDs retrieved from SQL Anywhere via
DBD::SQLAnywhere.
.PP
You probably don't want to be here, see
DBIx::Class::Storage::DBI::SQLAnywhere for information on the SQL Anywhere
driver.
.PP
Unfortunately when using DBD::SQLAnywhere, GUIDs come back in binary, the
purpose of this class is to transform them to text.
DBIx::Class::Storage::DBI::SQLAnywhere sets
cursor_class to this class by default.
It is overridable via your
connect_info.
.PP
You can use DBIx::Class::Cursor::Cached safely with this class and not lose
the GUID normalizing functionality,
::Cursor::Cached uses the underlying class data
for the inner cursor class.
